From 4da47369803f7fee486e25689e31cd0f71091ced Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 19:27:02 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] um: run BPF extable fixups for unresolvable vmalloc-range
 faults

segv() assumes any kernel-mode fault in [start_vm, end_vm) is a lazy
TLB flush, syncs, and retries the instruction. When the faulting
address has no present mapping, the retry can never make progress: a
deliberately faulting BPF load on an unmapped arena page whose kernel
address lands in the vmalloc range re-faults through this branch
forever, and the BPF extable fixup added for the other kernel-fault
paths never runs. verifier_arena_large hung the guest exactly this
way (perf sampling of the spinning UML process shows the
bpf_prog_test_run_syscall -> um_tlb_sync loop), while the smaller
verifier_arena arena happened to place its pages outside the vmalloc
window and took the already-fixed panic path instead.

After a successful um_tlb_sync(), check whether the address now has a
present PTE. If it does not, attempt the BPF extable fixup before
falling back to the legacy retry, which is preserved for non-BPF
faults.

All six verifier_arena_large subtests pass; the chunk previously had
to be denylisted.

Signed-off-by: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
---
 arch/um/kernel/trap.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/um/kernel/trap.c b/arch/um/kernel/trap.c
index aeda0640a..9dddbef1b 100644
--- a/arch/um/kernel/trap.c
+++ b/arch/um/kernel/trap.c
@@ -346,6 +346,7 @@ unsigned long segv(struct faultinfo fi, unsigned long ip, int is_user,
 	int err;
 	int is_write = FAULT_WRITE(fi);
 	unsigned long address = FAULT_ADDRESS(fi);
+	pte_t *pte;
 
 	if (!is_user && regs)
 		current->thread.segv_regs = container_of(regs, struct pt_regs, regs);
@@ -361,6 +362,20 @@ unsigned long segv(struct faultinfo fi, unsigned long ip, int is_user,
 			report_enomem();
 		if (err)
 			panic("Failed to sync kernel TLBs: %d", err);
+
+		/*
+		 * If the address still has no present mapping after the
+		 * sync, retrying the access cannot make progress. For a
+		 * deliberately faulting BPF load (e.g. an unmapped arena
+		 * page inside the vmalloc range) the fixup must run here,
+		 * or the same instruction re-faults through this branch
+		 * forever.
+		 */
+		pte = virt_to_pte(&init_mm, address);
+		if (!pte || !pte_present(*pte)) {
+			if (bpf_extable_fixup(ip, regs, mc))
+				goto out;
+		}
 		goto out;
 	}
 	else if (current->pagefault_disabled) {
-- 
